I opposed today's continuing resolution because we need to vote on permanent solutions on the urgent issues facing our nation, including community health clinics, opioid addiction, Dream, and worker pensions, among others.

As a member of the Appropriations Committee, and as an original #DreamAct author, I believe we must act NOW! We can’t keep kicking the can down the road on difficult decisions about government spending, and we can’t leave #Dreamers living in fear and uncertainty.

Some of my Senate colleagues voted for the CR because Sen. McConnell promised to take up legislation by Feb. 8 to keep our government running & address the plight of #Dreamers. But I am deeply skeptical. Sen. McConnell makes a lot of promises that he fails to keep.

Republicans control the House, Senate, and White House. Yet despite their full control of government, they are no closer to passing the spending bills that support programs and services important to America's families & military than they were 4 months ago.

This CR kicks the can down the road for the fourth time this fiscal year. Governing by repeated CRs leaves federal agencies such as our Defense Dept. unable to plan for the future or begin new initiatives. That undermines our nat'l security & leaves our homeland more vulnerable.

I opposed today's so-called "deal" on a 3-week continuing resolution. It does not get us any closer to a bipartisan budget agreement that enables us to finish our work on the FY 2018 approps bills, and it does not give us any meaningful certainty about a deal for the #Dreamers.
